<br>
Sometime last year, the US Army changed their headgear to black berets for all personnel.  Up until the change, only Rangers wore black berets.  After the change, Rangers changed theirs to a tan beret.<br>
<br>
I used to wear one of the &quot;old&quot; black berets.  When I first heard the news, I thought &quot;WTF???!!!&quot;.  The black beret symbolized certain things for me.  After a few days, I realized that it was just a hat and it didn't really mean anything.  Now when I see Army personnel wearing the black beret, I just smile ruefully.  There's still a twinge sometimes, but I'm mellow about it now.<br>
<br>
I'm the same way about a potential Ice Comet proc.  Call it a 1120 DD proc with a different name.  The words &quot;Ice Comet&quot; are just a symbol, but they do mean something to some people.  If the item is real, then I'll just smile ruefully when people tell me about it in game. <p>Brahma Atman
